In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. recognizes and appreciates the contributions and sacrifices made by military spouses. He acknowledges that although they may not wear a uniform, they play a crucial role in supporting and strengthening the military community and national security. The President emphasizes the resilience and diversity of military spouses, who understand the meaning of sacrifice and endure the hardships of having their partners deployed. He praises their ability to serve and create innovative solutions to address the challenges faced by the nation. President Biden also highlights his administration's commitment to supporting military families through initiatives focused on employment, education, and well-being. He calls upon the American people to honor military spouses through appropriate ceremonies and activities. The article concludes with a proclamation that May 6, 2022, is designated as Military Spouse Appreciation Day.